                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.—<name type="person" key="352">Corporal Richard H. Van Devine</name>, <name type="organization" key="153">Co. K, 1st New Jersey Infantry</name>, aged 28 years, received, at the battle of <name type="BATTLE" key="250"><choice><orig>Spottsylvania</orig><reg>Spotsylvania</reg></choice>, Virginia</name>,
                        <date type="injury" when="1864-05-12">May 12th, 1864</date>, a gunshot wound
                    of the scalp.  He was admitted, on <date type="admit" when="1864-06-11">June
                        11th</date>, to the <name type="hospital" key="165">Mount Pleasant
                        Hospital</name>, Washington, D. C., and, on <date type="transfer" when="1864-06-20">June 20th</date>, transferred to the <name type="hospital">Summit House
                            Hospital, Philadelphia</name>. At the period of his admission he was very much reduced,
                    and he died, on <date type="death" when="1864-07-10">July 10th, 1864</date>, "of
                    diarrhœa."   <name type="person" key="353">Surgeon J. H. Taylor</name>,
                        <name type="organization" key="132">U. S. V.</name>, records the case. </p>            
